Pre-Game Insights: This will be a first competitive fixture in charge for Kosovo boss Franco Foda, who signed up in February.
Foda, who guided Austria to the last 16 of Euro 2020, will be hoping he can take Kosovo into League B for the first time, as previous draws have not been kind to the Balkan side.
Romania come in fresh off the back of reaching the knockout stages at Euro 2024.
Legendary manager Mircea Lucescu, known for revolutionising Shakhtar Donetsk in a 12-year spell, is back at the helm 43 years after first taking charge between 1981 and 1986.
